<quiz>
  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Finding the distance and displacement of a delivery drone</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>A delivery drone is programmed to deliver two packages along a straight East-West flight path. The drone's motion is recorded as follows:</p>
<ul>
    <li>It flies \({@d1@}\) meters East to deliver the first package.</li>
    <li>It then turns around and flies \({@d2@}\) meters West to deliver the second package.</li>
</ul>

<p>
<ol>
    <li>What is the total distance travelled by the drone? [[input:ans1]] m [[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]]</li>
    <li>What is the drone's displacement from its starting point? [[input:ans2]] m [[validation:ans2]][[feedback:prt2]]</li>
</ol>
</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<b>1. Total Distance</b>
<p>Distance is the total length of the path travelled, regardless of direction:</p>
<p>
\(\begin{align}
\text{Distance} &= \text{Leg 1} + \text{Leg 2} \\
&= {@d1@} \text{ m} + {@d2@} \text{ m} \\
&= {@ta1@} \text{ m}
\end{align}\)
</p>

<b>2. Displacement</b>
<p>Displacement is the change in position (Final Position - Initial Position). Since the drone moved in opposite directions, we treat East as positive and West as negative:</p>
<p>
\(\begin{align}
\text{Displacement} &= \text{Final Position} - \text{Initial Position} \\
&= {@d1@} \text{ m} - {@d2@} \text{ m} \\
&= {@ta2@} \text{ m East}
\end{align}\)
</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
